<topic id="oxygen-editing-modes">
  <title>Editing Modes</title>
  <body>
    <p>To better suit the type of editing that you want to perform, <ph keyref="product"/> offers
      the following modes:<ul>
        <li><xref href="text-editor-specific-actions.dita#text-editor-specific-actions"
              ><uicontrol>Text</uicontrol></xref> - this mode presents the source of an XML
          document.</li>
        <li product="author authorEclipse developer developerEclipse editor editorEclipse"><xref
            href="grid-editor-introduction.dita#grid-editor-introduction"
              ><uicontrol>Grid</uicontrol></xref> - this mode displays an XML document as a
          structured grid of nested tables.</li>
        <li product="author editor authorEclipse editorEclipse"><xref
            href="tagless-editor.dita#tagless-editor"><uicontrol>Author</uicontrol></xref> - this
          mode enables you to edit in a WYSIWYG like editor.</li>
        <li><?oxy_comment_start author="steven_higgs" timestamp="20150506T085221+0300" comment="Needs to be linked.  Also, perhaps the whole &quot;XML Schema Diaram Editing Mode&quot; section should go in this chapter."?><uicontrol>Design</uicontrol>
          - this mode is found in the schema editor and represents the schema as a
          diagram.<?oxy_comment_end?></li>
      </ul></p>
